      "content": "Even a small amount of alcohol can interact unpredictably and dangerously with benzodiazepines like diazepam. The risk isn't minimal because alcohol increases the central nervous system depressant effects, making you more sedated than intended. To ensure your safety and the medicine works as intended, you should strictly avoid consuming any alcohol while taking diazepam. Always follow your doctor's instructions precisely regarding medication use.",
